<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1337">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/542.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Bundy Cole, manager of the National Bank of Nicaragua, left for the
                            United States April 22 to lay before the bankers the proposals for the
                            new loan which the Government is anxious to negotiate.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Weitzel</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>